    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "This is Hawaii Month\nHilo Hattie",
      "Beverages\nPLEASE BE OUR GUEST:\nBOURBON\nWHISKIES\nSCOTCH\nTENNESSEE\nCANADIAN\nCOCKTAILS\nUNITED'S VERY DRY MARTINI\n(GIN OR VODKA)\nOLD FASHIONED\nMANHATTAN\nSCREWDRIVER\nBLOODY MARY\nMAI TAI\nDAIQUIRI\nWHISKEY SOUR\nSPANISH SHERRY\nGIN\nVODKA\nRUM\nBEER\n* *\nTOMATO JUICE\nSOFT BEVERAGES\nHAWAIIAN MACADAMIA NUTS\nLIQUEURS\nCREME DE MENTHE\nBENEDICTINE AND BRANDY\nCOGNAC\nDRAMBUIE\nKAHLUA\nGALLIANO\nThe golden Tralian cordial a secret lens of hers disilled, acording to legend,\nMinors Will Not Be Served Liquor.\nSelected American Wines are served with this menu.\nthe new yorker\nMenu\nOn board today's early Now so sort\n- your the of the easie in che.\nGREATEWIDEWAY\nFRESHEBERRIES IN SEASON WILH CREAM\nCHILLED PINEAPPLE AND PAPAYA\nSELECTION OF FRUIT JUICES\nFOR YOUR BREAKFAST OR BRUNCH SELECTION:\nCORNED BEEF PATTY\nBROCHETTE OF BEEF, BERCY SAUCE\nHASHEBROWNED POTATOES\nFROM THE SKILLET:\nBROILED BUFFET HAM\nGRILLED MEDALLION ORDER\nBROILED LINK SAUSAGE\nASSORTED BREAKFAST ROLLS AND CAKES\nLater, as your California clock pur es he imping De lates so, il enio the many luncheon delights\nCREAM CHEESE, SMOKED SALMON\nSMOKED BEER TONGUE, ROASL BEEF. HAM, CORNED DECK AND\nCHOPPED CHICKEN LIVER\nGARNISHES\nASSORTED CHEESES AND CRACKERS\nA SELECTION OF BREADS AND ROLLS\nfollowed by a tempting\nDESSERT\nIt has been our pleasure to prepare this repast for your enjoyment.\nVili Nielser\nWilli Niederer, Chef de cuisine\nPlease accept our apology if your choice is not available."
